<br>
The body was moved and Monica could feel some of the signals in the nerves as she had before with Thomas but this was different. The signals were much stronger and unfiltered. She realized that quite slowly she was receiving sensation similar to having her own body. Wendy was surprised to be feeling some of the sensations also. It was the first time since Thomas had incorporated her into them.<br>
<br>
Thomas’ soul no longer with them, Monica and Wendy felt themselves merge even further into each other as the body lay in its coffin. Eventually their young embrace released them from the paralyzing bonds of Torpor. And they both knew that they were still in a great deal of jeopardy. <br>
<br>
With experience of healing and the power of the supernatural blood, Monica regenerated a new head and patiently moved her brain into place. She hadn’t realized that she re-grew her own visage and wasn’t quite aware of the monstrosity she had made as she’d moved her brain, making tissue corrections by touch only.<br>
<br>
She set to the task of digging out from the earth. The powers of bonecraft and fleshcraft let Monica alter her body to make quick work of the task but the thirst for blood became very powerful. They both knew they had to feed soon. The frenzy was near as their beasts beckoned them.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In the small hours of the morning, in an unmarked grave with a recent covering of sod, a sharply clawed, misshapen hand burst upward through the soil. And shortly thereafter a horribly disfigured face emerged after a second clawed hand broke the surface. <br>
<br>
Monica/Wendy pulled itself, naked and horrid, from the grave; a dark terrifying birth. The kids partying several hundred feet away didn’t hear the being emerge and they were surprised by its quiet approach.<br>
<br>
Monica/Wendy decided, after draining the two kids she’d lamed with sharp claws, to use the face and name of one of these victims. At the edge of the graveyard, the street yielded a truck parked on the roadside that was blessed with large mirrors. After the appropriate alterations were made she (now most definitely a he) returned to the bodies and took the identification of the young man.<br>
<br>
They laughed out loud to discover the boy’s first name being Jack. So Jack would be most fitting not only because of the past use of the name but because Monica and Wendy both preferred to remain in this male form due to the unjust male chauvinistic advantages within society both human and vampire.<br>
<br>
Hunting down four more victims before the night’s end, Jack replenished blood without further killings. The two that were in the graveyard were easily hidden inside a sepulcher and Jack left the graveyard to find the chantry.<br>
<br>
Spending a few nights outside the chantry an apprentice and a gargoyle finally came out to confront him. After asking meticulous questions about the new gargoyles and identifying himself as someone who knew Thomas most intimately, Jack was admitted and soon conferring with the Regent. Quickly the recognition was made with the Regent and the prior offer of service was reaffirmed along with the contract. <br>
<br>
Jack was immediately taken unto the Regent’s care and was counseled to deal with the loss of Thomas and the painful memories of their time together. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Jack would miss Thomas. So many stories and so many things Thomas had told him. All of his experiences of re-awakening in Nevada and relearning how to be in human society were so sad. To think that Thomas died thinking he was trying to keep the Sabbat away. Surely, someone else must have seen that.<br>
<br>
Nevertheless, Thomas’ viciousness was his downfall and impatience was his herald. Jack would not be so shortsighted. Survival and evolution were now paramount. Jack wished Thomas had listened.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Goodbye Thomas.<br>
<br>
(  o.o.c. not quite what anyone was expecting??  )<br>
