&quot;Intolerable!<br>
Irreguardless of the Regent and Nathan's direct instructions, Harry brown had seen too damn much. If any of those Dominating assholes like the Ventrue go digging into his head, they will clearly see what Powers we have!<br>
God damn, if the shit at the farm house weren't the biggest cluster fuck I've had the displeasure of participating in! And if Prophet figures out how those implants were removed, what the hell will keep him from betraying us to Marie?&quot;<br>
<br>
Monica:<br>
&quot;Prophet always going to the power like a moth to a flame says nothing about his dependability, I wonder if he'll string Marie out like he did with Nikkie. Too bad Herald has probably heard that Thomas is dead. Not that he'd want further dealings with us after he had been told that I was touted as speaking for the loonies and agreeing to kill Nikkie.&quot;<br>
<br>
Wendy:<br>
&quot;Well, I can see how it looked that way, Thomas didn't remain firm against being at the priogen meetings and speaking his mind. You give him too much credit.&quot;<br>
<br>
Monica:<br>
&quot;I can't help it. You know what I mean. He meant so much! It is so empty with him gone. It's like we were closer but didn't really realize it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Wendy:<br>
&quot;I miss him too...&quot;<br>
<br>
Both of them lost briefly in grief, Jack opens the text on the labratory counter and begins absorbing the details in the Feline Anatomy text. He takes in the sections on the hearing, nerve connection and paw sections. He spends hours going over the extending claws and the deep ear shapes and sensitive muscles that move the ears.<br>
<br>
Wendy:<br>
&quot;We should talk to the regent about Harry Brown. He cannot have the opportunity to inadvertantly betray us or our service to the clan. The higher circles wouldn't tolerate Eric's use of us in the current capacity. If we were converted completely, I'm sure they wouldn't object. But if they find out, his punishment would certainly include our demise.&quot;<br>
<br>
Monica:<br>
You and I both know that this is the best place to further our evolution and that we cannot walk away. You heard the discussion about our contract. The consequences are too great to take that risk. We must evolve!&quot;<br>
<br>
Wendy:<br>
I know. I'm just worried.&quot;<br>
<br>
The anatomical study pays off as Jack forms the hands of the current project construct. The ligament/tendon alterations and the nerve connections completed, he tests the muscle reaction with a low electrical pulse. Heads in the Labratory Turn with wide eyes as Jack laughs, delighted as the claws snap quickly forth from the fingertips, he brings the rest of the apprentices over to see the results and critique the effectiveness of their function. Then he discusses the alteration and shows them the proceedure.<br>
<br>
Finally he finishes the evenings work in a discussion of the function of the feline ears with the rest of the apprentices. He looks forward to the next evening's work. So many possibilities and so many things to test.<br>
